Azure File Sync enables organizations to synchronize on-premises Windows Servers with Azure Files.

It allows frequently accessed files to remain cached locally while less-used files are stored in Azure.

For example, a business can maintain local file server performance while leveraging Azure for scalability and backup.

# Real-Life Use Case:
A real-life use case is branch offices sharing centralized files while retaining local access speed.

# Real-Life Example:
Another example is disaster recovery where cloud copies protect against local failures.

Azure File Sync bridges on-premise and cloud environments efficiently.
